Dennis Naku, Port Harcourt Scores were injured while some residents fled after a gas plant went up in flames in Rumuodomaya community, Obio/Akpo Local Government Area of Rivers State on Saturday night. The explosion occurred about 8:45 pm with a loud sound which caused panic among residents of the area with some fleeing their homes in fear. READ ALSO: Fulani herdsmen remove finger, shatter woman’s jaw in Ogun The cause of the explosion could not be immediately ascertained as of the time of filing this report. The PUNCH reports that this came barely three weeks after a gas leak at a facility operated by the Nigeria Liquefied Natural Gas (NLNG) in Elibrada, Emuoha Local Government Area of the state. YOU MAY ALSO LIKE: Herdsmen kill, kidnap, rape our people – Ibarapa monarch Details later…